	abstract = {Pre-reflow Automated Optical Inspection(AOI) has been widely applied in the Printed Circuit Board(PCB) manufacturing to perform quality control. Two common problems in AOI-based recognition are how to realize the rapid inspection and how to predict the position and rotation angle of the PCB component quantitatively. However, the traditional—template matching algorithm tends to be exceedingly inefficient and non-robust. In this paper, we propose a new Convolutional Neural Network(CNN)-based method on the PCB resistor classification and pose prediction. For the problem of requiring a large number of labeled samples to train the CNN, we achieve the generation of the resistor dataset through extracting Region of Interest(ROI) and data augmentation. We employ the CNN which directly use the 11 types of resistor image as input and resistor type or pose error as predicted result. The classification accuracy is 99.60\%. And the method predicts a one-dimensional vector including horizontal position, vertical position and rotation angle, achieving 99.98\% accuracy. The processing time of a PCB resistor image is about 9ms. The experimental results have well demonstrated the effectiveness of our proposed method.},
