	abstract = {This paper proposes a novel circle detection framework integrated with an object detection network to accurately locate circular Printed Circuit Board (PCB) marks. By leveraging the object detection network for coarse localization, it becomes possible to effectively suppress complex backgrounds and reduce noise interference. In this work, the FasterNet network replaces the original backbone network in PicoDet, resulting in reduced latency and increased throughput. Furthermore, the incorporation of the ECA module enables more comprehensive capture of channel interactions while introducing minimal additional parameters and computational overhead. To achieve precise circle fitting, a novel point selection method named GOPS-CF, which relies on preset circle centers, is proposed. Moreover, the introduction of gradient descent and self-stop strategies enhances the stability and accuracy of the fitting results. Through comparative experiments and ablation studies compared to traditional methods, the superior performance of the proposed detection framework is demonstrated in terms of recognition success rate, positioning accuracy, and runtime. These findings underscore the significant implications of this framework for optimizing PCB automation production.},
